Attackers must capture Defender Comm Links(<I=G=MGO_LINK>) to download enemy data. Attackers win once the download is completed. Capturing multiple Comm Links speeds up the download.
Captured Comm Links scramble the radar of nearby enemies and can also be used as respawn points.
Close METAL GEAR ONLINE, and return to METAL GEAR SOLID V: THE PHANTOM PAIN.
Abandon match and all the players you are currently playing with, and go back to FREEPLAY.

Attackers must destroy or fulton the enemy Missile(<I=G=MGO_MISL>) before the round expires. To access the Missile, Attackers must first hack into the Terminals(<I=G=MGO_EVAC>) to deactivate the EM Barrier that's protecting the Missile from any incoming attacks or fultons.
Once the Terminals are hacked and the EM Barrier is deactivated, defenders can reactivate it by hacking back the Terminals.

The first team to reduce the other team's tickets to 0 wins. Enemy tickets can be reduced by killing or fultoning enemies.
Killing enemies adds to your bounty(<I=G=MGO_BOUNTY>) while Fultoning enemies reduces it. Fultoning an enemy adds their bounty to your team's tickets, which can result in a turnaround.
Are you sure you want to close METAL GEAR ONLINE, and return to METAL GEAR SOLID V: THE PHANTOM PAIN.?
Are you sure you want to abandon current match?

Armed only with camouflage, a combat knife and non-lethal weapons, Attackers must steal a Data Disc(<I=G=MGO_DISC>) and deliver it to the Evac Point(<I=G=MGO_EVAC>) before the round expires.
Defenders only hold lethal weapons and they must stop the attackers from stealing the Data Disc.
No respawns.
